The paper deals with concurrent data structures and their operations, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation of these data structures using atomic operations, which falls under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper proposes a condition called locality for set operations, which is related to distributed computing and falls under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of concurrent operations, which is related to systems and control and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a general framework for adding a linearizable iterator to data structures, which is related to software engineering and falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
